# SAP Integration Patterns — {{companyName}}

## When to Use
- Integrating with SAP S/4HANA, ECC, or BTP
- Working with SAP APIs (OData, RFC, BAPI)
- Managing SAP data models and business logic

## Integration Approaches
- **SAP BTP** — Cloud-native extensions and microservices
- **OData Services** — RESTful API access to SAP data
- **RFC/BAPI** — Direct function module calls for legacy systems
- **IDoc** — Document-based async messaging

## Best Practices
- Use SAP Cloud SDK for type-safe API access
- Follow SAP naming conventions for custom objects (Z/Y prefix)
- Test integrations against sandbox systems before production
- Handle SAP-specific error codes and retry patterns
- Document custom ABAP code with ADT annotations
